@startuml
title Communication Flow - Synchronous (HTTP/REST)

participant "Mobile App" as APP
participant "Load Balancer" as LB
participant "API Gateway" as GATEWAY
participant "Orchestrator" as ORCH
participant "Auth Service" as AUTH
participant "User Service" as USER
participant "Redis Cache" as CACHE
participant "Auth DB" as DB

== 1. Autenticación ==
APP ->> LB: POST /auth/login (credentials)
activate LB

LB ->> GATEWAY: Route to gateway
activate GATEWAY

GATEWAY ->> ORCH: [1] Forward request + trace-id
activate ORCH

ORCH ->> AUTH: [2] Validate credentials
activate AUTH

AUTH ->> CACHE: [3] Check token cache
activate CACHE
CACHE -->> AUTH: miss
deactivate CACHE

AUTH ->> DB: [4] Query user
activate DB
DB -->> AUTH: user data
deactivate DB

AUTH ->> AUTH: [5] Generate JWT token
AUTH ->> CACHE: [6] Store token (TTL: 1h)
activate CACHE
CACHE -->> AUTH: stored
deactivate CACHE

AUTH -->> ORCH: [7] Return JWT + refresh-token
deactivate AUTH

== 2. Obtener datos de usuario ==
ORCH ->> USER: [8] Get user profile
activate USER

USER ->> CACHE: [9] Check profile cache
activate CACHE
CACHE -->> USER: hit
deactivate CACHE

USER -->> ORCH: [10] Return cached profile
deactivate USER

ORCH -->> GATEWAY: [11] Aggregated response
deactivate ORCH

GATEWAY -->> LB: [12] Response + metadata
deactivate GATEWAY

LB -->> APP: [13] 200 OK + JWT + profile
deactivate LB

note over APP,DB
  **Benefits:**
  ✓ Immediate response
  ✓ Cache reduces latency
  ✓ Trace-id for debugging
  ✓ Circuit breaker at GATEWAY
  ✓ Rate limiting applied
  ✓ Each service owns its DB
end note

@enduml
